own in a curtiss aircraft boeing bought a glenn martin flying birdcage seaplane so called because of all the guywires holding it together and was taught to fly by glenn martin himself boeing soon crashed the birdcage and when martin informed boeing that replacement parts would not become available for months boeing realized he could build his own plane in that amount of time he and his friend cdr gc westervelt agreed to build a better airplane and soon produced the bw seaplane this first boeing airplane was assembled in a lakeside hangar located on the northeast shore of seattles lake union many of boeings early planes were seaplanes on april   the us declared war on germany and later in the year entered world war i on may   the company became the boeing airplane company with the us entering the war boeing knew that the us navy needed seaplanes for training so boeing shipped two new model cs to pensacola florida where the planes were flown for the navy the navy liked the model c and ordered  more the company moved its operations to a larger former shipbuilding facility known as boeing plant  located on the lower duwamish river washington state boeings original logo when world war i ended in  a large surplus of cheap used military planes flooded the commercial airplane market preventing aircraft companies from selling any new airplanes driving many out of business others including boeing started selling other products boeing built dressers counters and furniture along with flatbottom boats called sea sleds in  the boeing b flying boat made its first flight it accommodated one pilot and two passengers and some mail over the course of eight years it made international airmail flights from seattle to victoria british columbia on may   the boeing model  made its first flight it was the first plane to fly over mount rainier in  boeing entered competition against curtiss to develop a pursuit fighter for the us army air service although curtiss finished its design first and was awarded the contract boeing continued to develop its pw fighter that plane along with the boeing p fb fighter made boeing a leading manufacturer of fighters over the course of the next decade in  boeing built its model  mail plane for the us government to use on airmail routes in  an improved version of this plane was built the model a which won the us post offices contract to deliver mail between san francisco and chicago the a also had a passenger cabin that accommodated two that same year boeing created an airline named boeing air transport which merged a year later with pacific air transport and the boeing airplane company the first airmail flight for the airline was on july   the company changed its name to united aircraft and transport corporation in  and acquired pratt  whitney hamilton standard propeller company and chance vought united aircraft then purchased national air transport in  on july   the passenger boeing  biplane made its first flight with three engines it was boeings first plane built with the sole intention of being a passenger transport an upgraded version the a carrying eighteen passengers made its first flight in september  s and sedit in  the monomail a lowwing monoplane that carried mail was built built entirely out of metal it was very fast and aerodynamic and had retractable landing gear in fact its design was so revolutionary that the engines and propellers of the time could not handle the plane by the time controllable pitch propellers were developed boeing was building its model  airliner two monomails were built the second one the model  had a passenger cabin in  the boeing  was introduced the first truly modern airliner the  was an allmetal lowwing monoplane that was much faster safer and easier to fly than other passenger aircraft for example it was the first twin engine passenger aircraft that could fly on one engine in an era of unreliable engines this vastly improved flight safety boeing built the first sixty aircraft exclusively for its own united airlines subsidiarys operations this badly hurt competing airlines and was typical of the anticompetitive corporate behavior that the us government sought to prohibit at the time the air mail act of  prohibited airlines and manufacturers from being under the same corporate umbrella so the company split into three smaller companies – boeing airplane company united airlines and united aircraft corporation the precursor to united technologies as a result william boeing sold off his shares and left boeing clairmont claire l egtvedt who had become boeings president in  became the chairman as well he believed the companys future was in building bigger planes work began in  on boeing plant  to accommodate the production of larger modern aircraft boeing b assembly line in wichita kansas  boeing  stratocruiser shortly after an agreement with pan american world airways pan am was reached to develop and build a commercial flying boat able to carry passengers on transoceanic routes the first flight of the boeing  clipper was in june  it was the largest civil aircraft of its time with a capacity of  passengers on day flights and of  passengers on night flights one year later the first regular passenger service from the us to the uk was inaugurated subsequently other routes were opened so that soon pan am flew with the boeing  to destinations all over the world in  boeing completed work on its model  stratoliner this was the worlds first pressurizedcabin transport aircraft and it was capable of cruising at an altitude of  feet  m – above most weather disturbances it was based on the b using the same wings tail and engines during world war ii boeing built a large number of b and b bombers boeing ranked twelfth among united states corporations in the value of wartime production contracts many of the workers were women whose husbands had gone to war in the beginning of march  production had been scaled up in such a manner that over  planes were built each month to prevent an attack from the air the manufacturing plants had been covered with greenery and farmland items during these years of war the leading aircraft companies of the us cooperated the boeingdesigned b bomber was assembled also by lockheed aircraft corp and douglas aircraft co while the b was assembled also by bell aircraft co and by glenn l martin company after the war most orders of bombers were canceled and  people lost their jobs at boeingcitation needed the company aimed to recover quickly by selling its stratocruiser the model  a luxurious fourengine commercial airliner developed from the b however sales of this model were not as expected and boeing had to seek other opportunities to overcome the situationcitation needed the company successfully sold military derivatives of the stratocruiser such as the c adapted for troop transportation and the kc for aerial refuelingcitation needed sedit the boeing  in british overseas airways corporation boac livery  boeing developed military jets such as the b stratojet and b stratofortress bombers in the lates and into the s during the early s boeing used company funds to develop the – jet airliner demonstrator that led to the kc stratotanker and boeing  jetliner some of these were built at boeings facilities in wichita kansas which existed from  to  in the mids technology had advanced significantly which gave boeing the opportunity to develop and manufacture new products one of the first was the guided shortrange missile used to intercept enemy aircraft by that time the cold war had become a fact of life and boeing used its shortrange missile technology to develop and build an intercontinental missile in  boeing began delivery of its  the united states first commercial jet airliner in response to the british de havilland comet french sud aviation caravelle and soviet tupolev tu which were the worlds first generation of commercial jet aircraft with the  a fourengine passenger airliner the us became a leader in