hich boeing contributed with its experience in space rockets acquired during the apollo era boeing participated also with other products in the space program and was the first contractor for the international space station program during the decade several military projects went into production including boeing support of the stealth b bomber as part of an industry team led by northrop boeing built the outboard portion of the b stealth bomber wing the aft center fuselage section landing gear fuel system and weapons delivery system at its peak in  the b was the largest military program at boeing employing about  people the same year the national aeronautic association of the usa awarded the b design team the collier trophy for the greatest achievement in aerospace in america the first b rolled out of the bombers final assembly facility in palmdale california in november  and it flew for the first time on july   the avenger air defense system and a new generation of shortrange missiles also went into production during these years boeing was very active in upgrading existing military equipment and developing new ones boeing also contributed to wind power development with the experimental mod wind turbines for nasa and the united states department of energy and the modb for hawaii sedit air france er boeing was one of seven competing companies that bid for the advanced tactical fighter boeing agreed to team with general dynamics and lockheed so that all three companies would participate in the development if one of the three companies designs was selected the lockheed design was eventually selected and developed into the f raptor in april  boeing introduced the most modern commercial jet aircraft at the time the twinengine  with a seating capacity of approximately  to  passengers in a typical threeclass layout in between the  and the  the longest range twinengined aircraft in the world the  was the first boeing airliner to feature a flybywire system and was conceived partly in response to the inroads being made by the european airbus into boeings traditional market this aircraft reached an important milestone by being the first airliner to be designed entirely by using computeraided design cad techniques the  was also the first airplane to be certified for  minute etops at entry into service by the faa also in the mids the company developed the revamped version of the  known as the  nextgeneration or ng it has since become the fastestselling version of the  in history and on april   sales passed those of the classic  with a followup order for  aircraft from southwest airlines in  boeing chose to demolish the headquarters complex on east marginal way south instead of upgrading it to match new seismic standards the headquarters were moved to an adjacent building and the facility was demolished in  in  boeing was headquartered on east marginal way south by king county airport in seattle in  boeing acquired rockwells aerospace and defense units the rockwell business units became a subsidiary of boeing named boeing north american inc in august  boeing merged with mcdonnell douglas in a us billion stock swap under the name the boeing company however this name had actually been boeings official name previously adopted on may   following the merger the mcdonnell douglas md was renamed the boeing  and the production of the md was limited to the freighter version boeing introduced a new corporate identity with completion of the merger incorporating the boeing logo type and a stylized version of the mcdonnell douglas symbol which was derived from the douglas aircraft logo from the s aerospace analyst scott hamilton heavily criticized the ceo and his deputy philip m condit and harry stonecipher for thinking of their personal benefit first and with it causing the problems hitting boeing many years later instead of investing the huge cash reserve to build new airplanes they initiated a program to buy back boeing stock for more than us billionimportance –edit international space station boeing everett factory in  in january  boeing chose to expand its presence in another aerospace field of satellite communications by purchasing hughes electronics hughes space and communications company which had pioneered the satellite communications field in september  boeing moved its corporate headquarters from seattle to chicago chicago dallas and denver – vying to become the new home of the worlds largest aerospace concern – all had offered packages of multimilliondollar tax breaks its offices are located in the fulton river district just outside the loop chicago on october   boeing lost to its rival lockheed martin in the fierce competition for the multibilliondollar joint strike fighter contract boeings entry the x was rejected in favor of lockheeds x entrant boeing continues to serve as the prime contractor on the international space station and has built several of the major components boeing began development of the kc aerial refueling tanker in the early s italy and japan ordered four kcs each after development delays and faa certification boeing delivered the tankers to japan from  with the second kc following on march  to  italy received its four kc during  in  boeing ended production of the  after  aircraft were produced more advanced stretched versions of the  were beginning to compete against the  and the planned  was to fill much of the top end of the  market also that year boeing announced that the  the last civil aircraft to be designed by mcdonnell douglas would cease production in  the  was in danger of cancellation as well with the  replacing it but orders for the freighter version extended the program after several decades of success boeing lost ground to airbus and subsequently lost its lead in the airliner market in  multiple boeing projects were pursued and then canceled notably the sonic cruiser a proposed jetliner that would travel just under the speed of sound cutting intercontinental travel times by as much as  percent it was launched in  along with a new advertising campaign to promote the companys new motto forever new frontiers and to rehabilitate its image however the planes fate was sealed by the changes in the commercial aviation market following the september  attacks and the subsequent weak economy and increase in fuel prices subsequently boeing streamlined its production and turned its attention to a new model the boeing  dreamliner using much of the technology developed for the sonic cruiser but in a more conventional aircraft designed for maximum efficiency the company also launched new variants of its successful  and  models the  proved to be a highly popular choice with airlines and won a record number of prelaunch orders with delays to airbus a program several airlines threatened to switch their a orders to boeings new  version the  airbuss response to the  the a received a lukewarm response at first when it was announced as an improved version of the a and then gained significant orders when airbus promised an entirely new design the  program has encountered delays with the first flight not occurring until late  after regulatory approval boeing formed a joint venture united launch alliance with its competitor lockheed martin on december   the new venture is the largest provider of rocket launch services to the us government on august   boeing sold its rocketdyne rocket engine division to pratt  whitney on may   boeing agreed to purchase dallas texasbased aviall inc for  billion and retain  million in debt aviall inc and its subsidiaries aviall services inc and ils formed a wholly owned subsidiary of boeing commercial aviation services bcas realizing that increasing numbers of passengers have become reliant on their computers to stay in touch boeing introduced connexion by boeing a satellite based internet connectivity service that promised air travelers unprecedented access to the world wide web the company debuted the product to journalists in  receiving generally favorable reviews however facing competition from cheaper options such as cellular networks it proved too difficult to sell to most airlines in august  after a short and unsuccessful search for a buyer for the business boeing chose to discontinue the service on august   nasa selected boeing as the manufacturing contractor for the liquidfueled upper stage of the ares i rocket the stage based on both apollosaturn and space shuttle technologies was to be constructed at nasas michoud assembly facility near new orleans boeing constructed the sic stage of the saturn v rocket at this site in the s the boeing  dreamliner on its first flight boeing launched the  freighter in may  with an order from air france the freighter variant is based on the −lr other customers include fedex and emirates boeing officially announced in november  that it would produce a larger variant of the  the  in two versions commencing with the freighter version with firm orders for two cargo carriers the second version named the intercontinental is for passenger airlines both  versions feature a lengthened fuselage new advanced engines and wings and the incorporation of other technologies developed for the  boeing also received the launch contract from the us navy for the p poseidon multimission maritime aircraft an antisubmarine warfare patrol aircraft it has also received orders for the  aewc wedgetail aircraft the company has also introduced new extended range versions of the  these include the er and er the er is the latest and will extend the range of the – to a similar range as the successful – with the capability to fly more passengers due to the addition of two extra emergency exits the recordbreaking lr worldliner presented at the paris air show  the lr worldliner embarked on a wellreceived global demonstration tour in the second half of  showing off its capacity to fly farther than any other commercial aircraft on november   the lr set a world record for the longest nonstop flight the plane which departed from hong kong traveling to london took a longer route which included flying over the us it flew  nautical miles  km during its hour minute flight it was flown by pakistan international airlines pilots and pia was the first airline to fly the lr worldliner on august   boeing agreed to form a jointventure with the large russian titanium producer vsmpoavisma for the machining of titanium forgings the forgings will be used on the  program on december   boeing and vsmpoavisma created a joint venture ural boeing manufacturing and signed a contract on titanium product deliveries until  with boeing planning to invest  billion in russia over the next  years in february  boeing received a contract for  kc us air force tankers at a value of  billion the kc tankers are based on the kc graphic representation of the xm mounted combat system vehicle boeing jointly with science applications international corporation saic were the prime contractors in the us militarys future combat systems program the fcs program was canceled in june  with all remaining systems swept into the bct modernization program boeing works jointly with saic in the bct modernization program like the fcs program but the us army will play a greater role in creating baseline vehicles and will only contract others for accessories defense secretary robert m gates shift in defense spending to make tough choices about specific systems and defense priorities based solely on the national interest and then stick to those decisions over time hit boeing especially hard because of their heavy involvement with canceled air force projects unethical conductedit in may  the us air force announced it would lease  kc tankers to replace the oldest  of its kcs in november  responding to critics who argued that the lease was more expensive than an outright purchase the dod announced a revised lease of  aircraft and purchase of  in december  the pentagon announced the project was to be frozen while an investigation of allegations of corruption by one of its former procurement staffers darleen druyun who began employment at boeing in january was begun the fallout of this resulted in the resignation of boeing ceo philip m condit and the termination of cfo michael m sears harry stonecipher former mcdonnell douglas ceo and boeing coo replaced condit on an interim basis druyun pleaded guilty to inflating the price of the contract to favor her future employer and to passing information on the competing airbus a mrtt bid in october  she received a jail sentence for corruption in march  the boeing board forced president and ceo harry stonecipher to resign boeing said an internal investigation revealed a consensual relationship between stonecipher and a female executive that was inconsistent with boeings code of conduct and would impair his ability to lead the company james a bell served as interim ceo in addition to his normal duties as boeings cfo until the appointment of jim mcnerney as the new chairman president and ceo on june   industrial espionageedit in june  lockheed martin sued boeing alleging that the company had resorted to industrial espionage in  to win the evolved expendable launch vehicle eelv competition lockheed martin claimed that the former employee kenneth branch who went to work for mcdonnell douglas and boeing passed nearly  pages of proprietary documents to his new employers lockheed martin argued that these documents allowed boeing to win  of the  tendered military satellite launches in july  boeing was penalized with the pentagon stripping seven launches away from the company and awarding them to lockheed martin furthermore the company was forbidden to bid for rocket contracts for a twentymonth period which expired in march  in early september  it was reported that boeing was negotiating a settlement with the us department of justice in which it would pay up to  million to cover this and the darleen druyun scandal  euus agreement notesedit until the late s the us had a near monopoly in the large civil aircraft lca sector the airbus consortium created in  started competing effectively in the s at that stage the us became concerned about the european competition and the alleged subsidies paid by the european governments for the developments of the early models of the airbus family this became a major issue of contention as the european side was equally concerned by subsidies accruing to us lca manufacturers through nasa and defense programs the eu and the us started bilateral negotiations for the limitation of government subsidies to the lca sector in the late s negotiations were concluded in  with the signing of the ecus agreement on trade in large civil aircraft which imposes disciplines on government support on both sides of the atlantic which are significantly stricter than the relevant world trade organization wto rules notably the agreement regulates in detail the forms and limits of government support prescribes transparency obligations and commits the parties to avoiding trade disputes subsidy disputesedit in  the eu and the us agreed to discuss a possible revision of the  euus agreement provided that this would cover all forms of subsidies including those used in the us and in particular the subsidies for the boeing  the first new aircraft to be launched by boeing for  years in october  the us began legal proceedings at the wto by requesting wto consultations on european launch investment to airbus the us also unilaterally withdrew from the  euus agreement the us claimed airbus had violated a  bilateral accord when it received what boeing deemed unfair subsidies from several european governments airbus responded by filing a separate complaint contesting that boeing had also violated the accord when it received tax breaks from the us government moreover the eu also complained that the investment subsidies from japanese airlines violated the accord on january   boeing and airbus agreed that they would attempt to find a solution to the dispute outside of the wto however in june  boeing and the united states government reopened the trade dispute with the wto claiming that airbus had received illegal subsidies from european governments airbus has also responded to this claim against boeing reopening the dispute and also accusing boeing of receiving subsidies from the us government on september   the wto ruled that boeing had received billions of dollars in government subsidies boeing responded by stating that the ruling was a fraction of the size of the ruling against airbus and that it required few changes in its operations boeing has received  billion in support from washington state future conceptsedit in may  four concept designs being examined by boeing were outlined in the seattle times based on corporate internal documents the research aims in two directions lowcost airplanes and environmentalfriendly planes codenamed after the wellknown muppets a design team known as the green team concentrated primarily on reducing fuel usage all four designs illustrated rearengine layouts fozzie employs open rotors and offers a lower cruising speed beaker has very thin long wings with the ability to partially foldup to facilitate easier taxiing kermit kruiser has forward swept wings over which are positioned its engines with the aim of lowering noise below due to the reflection of the exhaust signature upward honeydew with its delta wing design resembles a marriage of the flying wing concept and the traditional tube fuselage as with most concepts these designs are only in the exploratory stage intended to help boeing evaluate the potentials of such radical technologies boeing recently patented its own force field technology also known as the shock wave attenuation system that would protect vehicles from shock waves generated by nearby explosions boeing has yet to confirm when they plan to build and test the technology –presentedit boeings wichita plant in  boeing ended its presence in kansas in – in  boeing completed its acquisition of argon st inc based in fairfax virginia argon st develops cisr command control communications computers intelligence surveillance and reconnaissance and combat systems on june   boeing announced its intent to acquire argon st as part of the companys strategy to expand its capabilities to address the cisr cyber and intelligence markets on november   it was reported that lion air has committed to ordering  boeing  max and  er airliners this order when finalized is worth  billion at list prices this is larger than any of boeings previous commercial aircraft sales the deal includes options for a further  airliners on january   boeing announced plans to close its facilities in wichita kansas with  workers before  more than  years after it was established boeing had employed as many as  people there boeing announced on may   it would cut  it jobs in seattle washington over the next three years in combination of layoffs attrition and relocation most of those will be relocated approximately  jobs each to st louis missouri and north charleston south carolina the company announced a  percent increase in profits—us billion total—for q  citing higher demand for commercial aircraft in april  boeing announced their long beach manufacturing facility would shut down by the end of the year the facility was responsible for building the boeing c globemaster iii military transport aircraft the last c  left final assembly in  the assembly site officially closed in february  and by april boeing had been auctioning factory manufacturing parts off some  jobs are affected nasa awarded contracts to boeing and spacex for transporting astronauts to the international space station in june  boeing announced that james mcnerney would step down as ceo to be replaced by boeings coo dennis muilenburg on july   in february  boeing announced that boeing president and ceo dennis muilenburg was elected the th chairman of the board succeeding james mcnerney in march  boeing announced to cut  jobs from its commercial airplane division by midyear boeing opened a  billion  acres  hectares factory in washington state on may   that will make carboncomposite wings for its x a key step toward delivering the first aircraft by  environmentedit environmental recordedit in  the ucla center for environmental risk reduction released a study showing that boeings santa susana field laboratory in the simi hills of eastern ventura county in southern california had been contaminated with toxic and radioactive waste the study found that air soil groundwater and surface water at the site all contained radionuclides toxic metals and dioxins air and water additionally contained perchlorate tce and hydrazines while water showed the presence of pcbs as well clean up studies and lawsuits are in progress jet biofuelsedit main articles aviation biofuel and algae fuel the airline industry is responsible for about  percent of greenhouse gases emitted by the us transportation sector aviations share of the greenhouse gas emissions is poised to grow as air travel increases and ground vehicles use more alternative fuels like ethanol and biodiesel boeing estimates that biofuels could reduce flightrelated greenhousegas emissions by  to  percent the solution blends algae fuels with existing jet fuel boeing executives said the company is informally collaborating with leading brazilian biofuels maker tecbio aquaflow bionomic of new zealand and other fuel developers around the world so far boeing has tested six fuels from these companies and will probably have gone through  fuels by the time were done evaluating them boeing was also joining other aviationrelated members in the algal biomass organization abo on june  air new zealand and boeing are researching the jatropha plant to see if it is a sustainable alternative to conventional fuel a twohour test flight using a – mixture of the new biofuel with jet a in the number one position rolls royce rb engine of  zknbs was successfully completed on december   the engine was then removed to be scrutinised and studied to identify any differences between the jatropha blend and regular jet a no effects to performances were found on august   boeing worked with the us air force to test the boeing c running on  percent jp  percent hydrotreated renewable jet fuel and  percent of a fischer–tropsch fuel with successful results electric propulsionedit for nasas n future airliner program boeing has determined that hybrid electric engine technology is by far the best choice for its subsonic design hybrid electric propulsion has the potential to shorten takeoff distance and reduce noise political contributions federal contracts advocacyedit in both  and  boeing was second on the list of top  us federal contractors with contracts totalling  billion and  billion respectively since  the company has agreed to pay  billion to settle  instances of misconduct including  million in  in relation to illegal hiring of government officials and improper use of proprietary information boeing is the top receiver of subsidies dubbed corporate welfare in the us based on  data with a total of  billion it also secured the highest ever tax breaks at the state level in  boeings  lobbying expenditure by the third quarter was  million  total  million in the  presidential election barack obama was by far the biggest recipient of campaign contributions from boeing employees and executives hauling in  – five times as much as john mccain and more than the top eight republicans combined boeing has a corporate citizenship program centered on charitable contributions in five areas education health human services environment the arts culture and civic engagementbetter source needed in  boeing spent  million in these areas through charitable grants and business sponsorships in february  boeing global corporate citizenship partnered with the insight labs to develop a new model for foundations to more effectively lead the sector that they servebetter source needed the company is a member of the us global leadership coalition a washington dcbased coalition of over  major companies and ngos that advocates for a larger international affairs budget which funds american diplomatic and development efforts abroad a series of us diplomatic cables show how us diplomats and senior politicians intervene on behalf of boeing to help boost the companys sales in  and  the company benefited from over  billion of longterm loan guarantees helping finance the purchase of their commercial aircraft in countries including brazil canada ireland and the united arab emirates from the exportimport bank of the united states some  percent of the total loan guarantees the bank made in the period in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized boeing for spending  million on lobbying and not paying taxes during – instead getting  million in tax rebates despite making a profit of  billion laying off  workers since  and increasing executive pay by  percent to  million in  for its top five executives divisionsedit boeing plant in ridley park pennsylvania the two largest divisions are boeing commercial airplanes and boeing defense space  security bds boeing capital boeing commercial airplanes bca boeing defense space  security bds phantom works engineering test  technology boeing research  technology boeing test  evaluation intellectual property management information technology environment health and safety boeing shared services group boeing realty boeing travel management company boeing supplier management employment numbersedit the companys employment count is listed on its website below employment by division july   group employees boeing commercial airplanes bca  boeing defense space  security bds  corporate  finance  shared services  other  total company  employment by location july   location employees alabama  arizona  california  missouri  oklahoma  p