alifornia in november  and it flew for the first time on july   the avenger air defense system and a new generation of shortrange missiles also went into production during these years boeing was very active in upgrading existing military equipment and developing new ones boeing also contributed to wind power development with the experimental mod wind turbines for nasa and the united states department of energy and the modb for hawaii sedit air france er boeing was one of seven competing companies that bid for the advanced tactical fighter boeing agreed to team with general dynamics and lockheed so that all three companies would participate in the development if one of the three companies designs was selected the lockheed design was eventually selected and developed into the f raptor in april  boeing introduced the most modern commercial jet aircraft at the time the twinengine  with a seating capacity of approximately  to  passengers in a typical threeclass layout in between the  and the  the longest range twinengined aircraft in the world the  was the first boeing airliner to feature a flybywire system and was conceived partly in response to the inroads being made by the european airbus into boeings traditional market this aircraft reached an important milestone by being the first airliner to be designed entirely by using computeraided design cad techniques the  was also the first airplane to be certified for  minute etops at entry into service by the faa also in the mids the company developed the revamped version of the  known as the  nextgeneration or ng it has since become the fastestselling version of the  in history and on april   sales passed those of the classic  with a followup order for  aircraft from southwest airlines in  boeing chose to demolish the headquarters complex on east marginal way south instead of upgrading it to match new seismic standards the headquarters were moved to an adjacent building and the facility was demolished in  in  boeing was he