ondit and harry stonecipher for thinking of their personal benefit first and with it causing the problems hitting boeing many years later instead of investing the huge cash reserve to build new airplanes they initiated a program to buy back boeing stock for more than us billionimportance –edit international space station boeing everett factory in  in january  boeing chose to expand its presence in another aerospace field of satellite communications by purchasing hughes electronics hughes space and communications company which had pioneered the satellite communications field in september  boeing moved its corporate headquarters from seattle to chicago chicago dallas and denver – vying to become the new home of the worlds largest aerospace concern – all had offered packages of multimilliondollar tax breaks its offices are located in the fulton river district just outside the loop chicago on october   boeing lost to its rival lockheed martin in the fierce competition for the multibilliondollar joint strike fighter contract boeings entry the x was rejected in favor of lockheeds x entrant boeing continues to serve as the prime contractor on the international space station and has built several of the major components boeing began development of the kc aerial refueling tanker in the early s italy and japan ordered four kcs each after development delays and faa certification boeing delivered the tankers to japan from  with the second kc following on march  to  italy received its four kc during  in  boeing ended production of the  after  aircraft were produced more advanced stretched versions of the  were beginning to compete against the  and the planned  was to fill much of the top end of the  market also that year boeing announced that the  the last civil aircraft to be designed by mcdonnell douglas would cease production in  the  was in danger of cancellation as well with the  replacing it but orders for the freighter version extended the program after several decades of