 numbers of passengers have become reliant on their computers to stay in touch boeing introduced connexion by boeing a satellite based internet connectivity service that promised air travelers unprecedented access to the world wide web the company debuted the product to journalists in  receiving generally favorable reviews however facing competition from cheaper options such as cellular networks it proved too difficult to sell to most airlines in august  after a short and unsuccessful search for a buyer for the business boeing chose to discontinue the service on august   nasa selected boeing as the manufacturing contractor for the liquidfueled upper stage of the ares i rocket the stage based on both apollosaturn and space shuttle technologies was to be constructed at nasas michoud assembly facility near new orleans boeing constructed the sic stage of the saturn v rocket at this site in the s the boeing  dreamliner on its first flight boeing launched the  freighter in may  with an order from air france the freighter variant is based on the −lr other customers include fedex and emirates boeing officially announced in november  that it would produce a larger variant of the  the  in two versions commencing with the freighter version with firm orders for two cargo carriers the second version named the intercontinental is for passenger airlines both  versions feature a lengthened fuselage new advanced engines and wings and the incorporation of other technologies developed for the  boeing also received the launch contract from the us navy for the p poseidon multimission maritime aircraft an antisubmarine warfare patrol aircraft it has also received orders for the  aewc wedgetail aircraft the company has also introduced new extended range versions of the  these include the er and er the er is the latest and will extend the range of the – to a similar range as the successful – with the capability to fly more passengers due to the addition of two extra emergency exits the rec