ere the last two digits of the series designator are replaced by the two digit alphanumeric boeing customer code for example  representing a  originally ordered by pan american world airways boeing customer code  or h representing a  originally ordered by southwest airlines boeing customer code h unlike other models the  uses a single digit to designate the series for example  this convention was followed in the development of the newest version of the  the  along with the  max and x series additional letters are sometimes appended to the model name as a suffix including er to designate an extended range version such as the er or lr to designate a long range version for example lr other suffix designators include f for freighter f c for convertible aircraft that can be converted between a passenger and freighter configuration c and m for combi aircraft that are configured to carry both passengers and freight at the same time m m passenger aircraft that are originally manufactured as passenger aircraft and later converted to freighter configuration by boeing carry the suffix bcf designating a boeing converted freighter bcf aircraft in production or developmentedit product list and details aircraft model number built description capacity first flight variants in production outofproduction variants   twin‑engine single aisle short to mediumrange narrowbody – april     er bbj c  aewc p  max   c  adv     er    heavy four‑engine partial double deck twin–aisle main deck single–aisle upper deck medium to longrange widebody – february   i f bbj  sr b  f c sp m  m sr  m d f er erf vc e yal   heavy twinengine twin aisle medium to longrange widebody – september   er f kc kc  er  er e   heavy twinengine twin aisle medium to longrange ultra longrange lr widebody – june   er freighter  er lr    heavy twinengine twin aisle longrange widebody – december      bbj future airliner models expected eis type description notes  x new  series with the lengthened x and extra long range x it 